Since the while loop is `while (true)` and contains no `break` statements, the only way the loop can exit is by fulfilling this condition, which is already returning from the method

    if (day &gt; 3) {
        return day;
    }

Therefore the `return day` at the bottom of the method is not possible to reach.

Just remove that line `return day;` at the bottom of the method. Provided your logic is correct and `day` will eventually be greater than 3, you don&#39;t need it.

Alternatively, choose a proper condition rather than `while (true)`, or add a break statement.

